-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() RPS1 = input.getNumber(1) RPS2 = input.getNumber(2) RPS3 = input.getNumber(3)
endRPS = math.max(RPS1, RPS2, RPS3)
if (RPS1+RPS2+RPS3)==0 then output.setNumber(1, 0) else if RPS1>0 and endRPS>RPS1 then endRPS = RPS1 end if RPS2>0 and endRPS>RPS2 then endRPS = RPS2 end if RPS3>0 and endRPS>RPS3 then endRPS = RPS3 end output.setNumber(1, endRPS) end end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() Drossel = input.getNumber(1) UD = input.getNumber(2)
if math.abs(UD) > 0 then tick = tick-1 end
if math.abs(UD) > 0.5 then if UD < 0 and Drossel>=0.01 then Drossel = Drossel-0.01 end if UD > 0 and Drossel<=0.99 then Drossel = Drossel+0.01 end end
output.setNumber(1, Drossel) end

function onTick() DOWN = input.getBool(1) UP = input.getBool(2) CurrentClutch = input.getNumber(1) if CurrentClutch<=0.8 and UP == true then CurrentClutch = CurrentClutch+0.2 end if CurrentClutch>=0.2 and DOWN == true then CurrentClutch = CurrentClutch-0.2 end output.setNumber(1, CurrentClutch) end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() WindSpeed = math.floor(input.getNumber(1)) -- m/s WindDir = input.getNumber(2)*360+180 WindLabel = 0 if WindSpeed>=10 then WindLabel = 5 end if WindSpeed>=100 then WindLabel = 10 end end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight()
screen.drawClear() screen.setColor(28, 170, 214) -- Set background to sky blue screen.drawRectF(0, 0, w, h)
screen.setColor(25, 25, 50)
screen.drawText(37, 24, WindSpeed) screen.drawText(44+WindLabel, 24, "m/s")
screen.drawCircle(13, 12, 1)
--Forward if WindDir<=60 or WindDir>=300 then screen.drawLine(13, 9, 13, 3) screen.drawLine(12, 5, 15, 5) screen.drawLine(11, 6, 12, 6) screen.drawLine(15, 6, 16, 6) end
--Backward if WindDir<=240 and WindDir>=120 then screen.drawLine(13, 15, 13, 21) screen.drawLine(12, 19, 15, 19) screen.drawLine(11, 18, 12, 18) screen.drawLine(15, 18, 16, 18) end
--Left if WindDir<=330 and WindDir>=210 then screen.drawLine(10, 12, 4, 12) screen.drawLine(6, 11, 6, 14) screen.drawLine(7, 10, 8, 10) screen.drawLine(7, 14, 8, 14) end
--Right if WindDir<=150 and WindDir>=30 then screen.drawLine(16, 12, 22, 12) screen.drawLine(20, 11, 20, 14) screen.drawLine(19, 10, 18, 10) screen.drawLine(19, 14, 18, 14) end
end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() EmergencyMod = input.getBool(1) WS = input.getNumber(1) AD = input.getNumber(2)
LF = false LS = false LR = false RF = false RS = false RR = false soundTurning = false soundBack = false
if AD<-0.1 or EmergencyMod==true then LF = true soundTurning = true end if AD>0.1 or EmergencyMod==true then RF = true soundTurning = true end
if AD<-0.1 then LS = true LR = true soundTurning = true end if AD>0.1 then RS = true RR = true soundTurning = true end
if WS<-0.1 or EmergencyMod==true then LR = true RR = true soundTurning = true end
if WS<-0.1 then soundTurning = false soundBack = true end
output.setBool(1, LF) output.setBool(5, LS) output.setBool(3, LR) output.setBool(2, RF) output.setBool(6, RS) output.setBool(4, RR) output.setBool(7, soundTurning) output.setBool(8, soundBack) end

function onTick() BaseNumber = input.getNumber(1) ToR = input.getNumber(3) N = input.getNumber(3) answer = false
if ToR==0 and BaseNumber==N then answer = true end if ToR==1 and BaseNumber>N then answer = true end if ToR==-1 and BaseNumber<N then answer = true end
output.setNumber(1, answer) end
